[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "basic_bidding/minor_suit_openings"]
[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

With a 5-card and a 4-card Minor you open the 5-card. Partner responds 1NT.  

With only 14 points a pass might be the best bid. But with doubletons in both Majors, knowing partner does not have 4 of either, you elect to bid 2\C. Partner now surprises you and bids 3\C. It's your bid. 

Partner evidently found some hidden treasure when he revalued! But you still have only 16 points at the most so you pass.}

